Tom Emerson wrote:
&gt;
&gt; I&#39;m exploring the JMX interface for remote control of Heritrix in more 
&gt; depth.
&gt;
&gt; The &#39;addJob&#39; method takes a &quot;seed&quot; parameter, which presumably is a 
&gt; list of seeds to use for the crawl. I assumed that I could give the 
&gt; path to an order file and the list of seeds in this argument, and 
&gt; Heritrix would create the seeds.txt file for me. But this isn&#39;t the 
&gt; case (at least in CVS HEAD). It would appear that in addition to the 
&gt; path to the order you have to have the seeds file in place so that the 
&gt; reference in the order can find it. What then is the purpose of the 
&gt; seeds param in the JMX interface?
&gt;
&gt; I noticed that you can pass the path to a JAR file containing the 
&gt; order and seed files. How do I refer to the seeds in the order so that 
&gt; they will be found?
&gt;











Submit a jar that has a seeds file sitting beside the order file.  In 
the order file, the path-to-the-seeds should be the default 
&#39;seeds.txt&#39;.  I know this works (Its how Archive-It sends jobs to remote 
crawlers).  

I haven&#39;t looked at this in a while but IIRC correctly, passing other 
than default path-to-seeds in the order.xml was problematic (And looking 
at the code, it looks like the &#39;seeds&#39; argument is ignominiously dropped 
on certain traces down through addJob).  I&#39;ll add an issue for clearing 
up the API hereabouts.

Go easy Tom,
St.Ack





